history.content:
I'm a recently declared CS major looking to complete the degree in 3 semester. I'm having difficulty enrolling in courses I need to graduate. I've finished all requirements except EE16A, 2 technical electives, and 5 upper div EECS courses. I'd like to get 3 requirements out of the way next semester, so I've enrolled in 3 technical electives and wait listed 2 upperdiv CS's (I'm swapping one tech elec with cs170).

I'm very high on the wait lists for both CS courses (position ~300 in CS170). Does anyone have advice for how to get 3 requirements out of the way next semester? I can't try to enroll in EE16A without dropping a technical elective?

EDIT: Is it possible to enroll directly into EE16A without official CS/EECS declation?
